<subSubSection id="B3DA74A0CEAF3229CAAF26DAEC73F160" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="note 1">
<paragraph id="61E75E7E3E52BADFFC14C41E82A6189B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note 1.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BA42644C1A56C76C68F9BA8F38F6172B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="D29B6E3C2DEB842C61C4887E2F684F13" author="Dandy, JE" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="123 - 133" refId="B18" refString="Dandy, JE, 1928c. New or noteworthy Chinese Magnolieae. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh 16 (77): 123 - 133" title="New or noteworthy Chinese Magnolieae." volume="16" year="1928 c">Dandy (1928c</bibRefCitation>
: 130) provides relevant background information concerning the type collections of 
<taxonomicName id="7B5A6B6B285B12563CA859884EC81EEC" class="Gastropoda" family="Sinuspiridae" genus="Michelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Michelia platypetala" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis id="BBFF9A5182B2D1888DFE3FD958A384BC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Michelia platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0D9ED8131C7602F2E09FA6E0AB27E772" genus="M." lsidName="M. fallax" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="fallax">
<emphasis id="768CD7C9E23DF292F6744FE6B228EE98" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. fallax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the same general locality in Hunan Province in consecutive years and how they were both initially confused as the former species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E4443002FD80082FA03B99A0658929B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="note 2">
<paragraph id="14706FFA3E1D8C8C9538FE104C1F7CA6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note 2.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F9AC31F2D893A765DC86CFB03535DFF3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
As recorded in the synonymy section preceding Note 1, 
<taxonomicName id="A145947BA3582028A7B53B294072CF3A" class="Gastropoda" family="Sinuspiridae" genus="Michelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Michelia platypetala" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis id="224A1383388849A63F9F3A40A2342E33" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Michelia platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is noted as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="937A97C6621581C38D123F4D7C9BC503" genus="M." lsidName="M. cavaleriei" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cavaleriei">
<emphasis id="D14210231348E9D0196ED673A5161B69" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. cavaleriei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and has been made a variety of both 
<taxonomicName id="BA0B2D0E1137A15B48E08BB2E3A890C9" authorityName="Dunn (Figlar) var. rubicunda (T. P. Yi &amp; J. C. Fan) C. B. Callaghan &amp; S. K. Png" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Dunn (Figlar) var. rubicunda (T. P. Yi &amp; J. C. Fan) C. B. Callaghan &amp; S. K. Png" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Magnolia maudiae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maudiae">
<emphasis id="C15C70A40EC67095656E3AB77E122B22" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Magnolia maudiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9DD0F4A56431E8FD119D2BFB8C0BD062" class="Gastropoda" family="Sinuspiridae" genus="Michelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Michelia cavaleriei" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cavaleriei">
<emphasis id="C45C501C97666892521D88FF9D844D53" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Michelia cavaleriei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 2001 and 2008 publications with a noted elevational range of 1200-1500 m despite 
<normalizedToken id="2AE907ED5270938B0B1372E1CFB2617F" originalValue="Handel-Mazzetti’s">Handel-Mazzetti's</normalizedToken>
type collection being made at ca. 950 metres. However, 
<taxonomicName id="E2C5958A062DD5FE524B79F6AEE656FE" genus="M." lsidName="M. platypetala" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis id="F0B5D5B38E7F9D4DC94137A57FA69D81" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
retains its species status in 
<bibRefCitation id="FFB63BF1E0D3FC923F360353E934BFBD" author="Law, YW" journalOrPublisher="Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://frps.iplant.cn/" refId="B48" refString="Law, YW, Lo, HS, Wu, YF, Chang, BN [Eds], 1996. Magnoliaceae. In: Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae Tomus 30(1) Angiospermae, Dicotyledoneae: Menispermaceae, Magnoliaceae. Science Press, Beijing, 82-273. http://frps.iplant.cn/" title="Magnoliaceae. In: Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae Tomus 30 (1) Angiospermae, Dicotyledoneae: Menispermaceae, Magnoliaceae. Science Press, Beijing, 82 - 273." url="http://frps.iplant.cn/" year="1996">Law et al. (1996</bibRefCitation>
: 177), 
