<paragraph id="21E7946E775C836B296FE41F6FEC7244" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note 3.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="40A74DC26BCC56FC73B34D7F265E3373" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="95879C166975586780EB1A8C8ADC8630" author="Grimshaw, J" journalOrPublisher="International Dendrology Society / Kew Publishing, Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B34" refString="Grimshaw, J, Bayton, R, 2009. New Trees-Recent Introductions to Cultivation. International Dendrology Society/ Kew Publishing, Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="New Trees-Recent Introductions to Cultivation." year="2009">Grimshaw and Bayton (2009</bibRefCitation>
: 500) record a personal communication received from Richard Figlar in 2007 advising that &quot;this taxon (
<taxonomicName id="81ED3EA33C693D8EBBA2040E81796693" authorityName="Sima" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Hand. - Mazz." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Magnolia maudiae subsp. var. var. platypetala" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="maudiae" subSpecies="var." variety="platypetala">Magnolia maudiae var. platypetala</taxonomicName>
) probably ought to be recognised at the specific level, as 
<taxonomicName id="3A2A6D5432D8D15FDE8D2FA6D0D5CA0C" authorityName="C. B. Callaghan &amp; S. K. Png" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="C. B. Callaghan &amp; S. K. Png" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Magnolia platypetala" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis id="E7718117681DC67894C1C382BDA6825D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Magnolia platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as it differs considerably from 
<taxonomicName id="12648152801FB7577BEB14381D2EF349" genus="M." lsidName="M. maudiae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="maudiae">
<emphasis id="EF2BF7E78648200F6B67292625A58E9D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. maudiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both in its hairiness and its later bud-break&quot;. 
<bibRefCitation id="A9FE6B7A38813A8474B05D1DA5782F27" author="Sima, YK" journalOrPublisher="PhD Thesis, Yunnan University, Kunming" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://www.docin.com/p-1050989203.html" refId="B71" refString="Sima, YK, 2011. A Taxonomic Revision of the Magnoliaceae from China. PhD Thesis, Yunnan University, Kunming, http://www.docin.com/p-1050989203.html" title="A Taxonomic Revision of the Magnoliaceae from China." url="http://www.docin.com/p-1050989203.html" year="2011">Sima (2011</bibRefCitation>
: 327), illustrates the contrasting difference between the indumentum of the undersurfaces of the leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="2CD648225C49132457F3453344F66C3C" genus="M." lsidName="M. platypetala" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis id="3428349F6CA7C96438162200F240963D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Plate 3-4H) and that of the leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="37D5457DC7D65F3AB8EB19A4CC895740" genus="M." lsidName="M. maudiae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="maudiae">
<emphasis id="30F4ED9B69A7F7C370412775054A276E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. maudiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Plate 3-4C). Additionally, in a study by 
<bibRefCitation id="C61007474F5A717A8859F979A19D9706" author="Zhang, XH" journalOrPublisher="Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="167 - 190" publicationUrl="http://www.plantsystematics.com/CN/article/downloadArticleFile.do?attachType=PDF&amp;id=225" refId="B88" refString="Zhang, XH, Xia, NH, 2007. Leaf architecture of subtribe Micheliinae (Magnoliaceae) and its taxonomic significance. Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica 45 (2): 167 - 190, http://www.plantsystematics.com/CN/article/downloadArticleFile.do?attachType=PDF&amp;id=225" title="Leaf architecture of subtribe Micheliinae (Magnoliaceae) and its taxonomic significance." url="http://www.plantsystematics.com/CN/article/downloadArticleFile.do?attachType=PDF&amp;id=225" volume="45" year="2007">Zhang and Xia (2007)</bibRefCitation>
on leaf architecture and its taxonomic significance in respect of subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="48F19DB577570A37516BDBA699976F8A" authorityName="Y.W.Law" authorityYear="1984" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Micheliinae">Micheliinae</taxonomicName>
of 
<taxonomicName id="5E94B7BA7CF3F81D7E366EBE3CD87E40" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="M." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Magnoliaceae</taxonomicName>
, the pronounced contrast in the leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="C4891F29CCD7847779F825A8BCE9C23D" class="Gastropoda" family="Sinuspiridae" genus="Michelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Michelia platypetala" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis id="0723C2A6E0537C2DDB9297E722E7B6FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Michelia platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9F4D37794E8A3F9D0DF3DFD932322E58" genus="M." lsidName="M. cavaleriei" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cavaleriei">
<emphasis id="213A6D6E73D76FF4DC4BAF8A8513ECCB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. cavaleriei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as revealed by stereoscopic magnified imaging (shown at figs. 36 and 37 in their paper), resulted in these authors concluding that these two taxa should be recognised as independent species&quot;. It is apparent that there is now an almost unanimous consensus of the species status of 
<taxonomicName id="928DA79C937BB0B3FA48CAFCCB905FBB" class="Gastropoda" family="Sinuspiridae" genus="Michelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Michelia platypetala" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis id="3707D4B837F21B8CAD9EE910F22DA170" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Michelia platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is confirmed by the comparison of its morphological features with those of 
<taxonomicName id="FD885C853806E88F117F4AF1FB6C859F" genus="M." lsidName="M. cavaleriei" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cavaleriei">
<emphasis id="4396D0054A3E8D6F1A053E459A63CFAB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. cavaleriei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compiled in Table 
<tableCitation id="085B67F7CB5DBEF008BBE7298D9B7A76" captionStart="Table 5" captionStartId="T5" captionText="Table 5. Differentiating features of the species Michelia platypetala and M. cavaleriei." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0F9202D236A02A5D5F1C663AE2BE68D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableUuid="0F9202D236A02A5D5F1C663AE2BE68D9">5</tableCitation>
below. In view of its distinctive characteristics and accepting the majority recognition by the above-mentioned Chinese authors of 
<taxonomicName id="99327C382D37C35604A030C15E000152" class="Gastropoda" family="Sinuspiridae" genus="Michelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Michelia platypetala" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis id="D7DB845D85DA86BEEF9DE9104A3C4AC5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Michelia platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a genuine species, it is here transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="5AECB0CE3C93197B03BA1219F9ABBAC0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Magnolia" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="31F3AB1496B9D21ECFBA6F4FA3659DAA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Magnolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a consequence of the past reduction of the remaining genera of subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="2A96E2AD0FD33D6D1AB3377C0C2851B6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Magnolioideae">Magnolioideae</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="8133F51EC1D2E3199EFD2676C52A3BA1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Magnolia" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D08CE27E7A1BF52A86C63ECF53FE5192" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Magnolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="0F9202D236A02A5D5F1C663AE2BE68D9" ID-Table-UUID="0F9202D236A02A5D5F1C663AE2BE68D9" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0F9202D236A02A5D5F1C663AE2BE68D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Table 5" startId="T5">
